Frank FULLER, Appellant, v. J. M. McCAULEY, Warden, Washington State Penitentiary, Appellee. No. 8660. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Jan. 14, 1938. Frank Fuller, in pro. per. G. W. Hamilton, Atty. Gen., and W. A. Toner, Asst. Atty. Gen., for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, MATHEWS, and HANEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The order herein appealed from, 20 F.Supp. 206, is affirmed upon the authority of Hall v. People of State of California, 9 Cir., 79 F.2d 132, and cases there cited. See, also, McCauley v. Palmer, 9 Cir., 91 F.2d 1017; McCauley v. Goldberg, 9 Cir., 91 F.2d 1016; and McCauley v. Mehlhorn, 9 Cir., 91 F.2d 1017.
